There’s been an enormous staff turnover since covid - I know maybe 3 lecturers now? And it would be challenging to discuss my mental health with them.

And to speak to uni mental health support in approx 1 month. Staying on placement was the only real option. Now? I’ve had 5 tutors this year alone. I’ve spoken to my current tutor once. How do I tell her if I’m sick?

Especially when they have the power to fail you. I told uni last year when I was suicidal - by the time a tutor could talk to me, I had 1 week of placement left and the solutions offered were: leave placement (increasing stress because you have to make the hours up elsewhere)

From my own experience: concurrent placements and assignments mean you never have time to rest. Placement is stressful trying to fit in to new teams every few weeks - admitting mental ill health to people you don’t know is HARD. https://t.co/qowfaSjPnw
